gridguess - classroom board game
================================
gridguess is a classroom board game designed to be both fun and minimal work
to prepare games. It functions on a grid of unknown questions displayed in
columns with each slot defined by a formatted text file.

Requirements
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup

Edit gg.h to configure the path to a font.
If you need to download a font, go to [https://fonts.google.com].

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install gridguess (if
necessary as root):

    make clean install


Running gridguess
-----------------
Run the binary at the command line with the properly formatted text file as
the second argument. Either close the main window or interrupt the command
line to quit.
